==English==

===Etymology===
from the threat ''you are going to be wearing your ass for a hat''

Possibly originated back in the 1990s on forums to get around language filters. "Asshole" would be flagged as "a******" but the filters wouldn't catch "asshat."

Another plausible explanation is that means that someone has their head up their ass, hence is wearing their ass as a hat. This theory would appear to apply equally well to someone who has their head up someone else's ass.

===Noun===
